<br>
GROUPED<br>
-Tash<br>
-Haste/Slow/Cripple<br>
-Boon/Tricksters/Nuke<br>
-Rune/Mana-tap/(Other)<br>
-Gate<br>
-Stun<br>
-Mez<br>
-Root<br>
<br>
I will always tash of course. Haste I usually mem only when I need to cast it. Slow and Cripple only if there is no Shaman in the party. Tanks love Boon and I love giving it to them (get your mind out of the gutter <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Tricksters help main tank keeping aggro, or at least in theory it does. I usually nuke before mob dies if I have spare mana. Gate is obvious although very occasionally I won't mem gate. Mez is obvious. There are only a crumb-sized amount of situations where we don't need mez memmed.<br>
<br>
Oooooh my favorite level 4 root spell. I still use it at 55. With specialize alteration and spell haste, I am the fasted rooter in the west! You all know that root is extremely random. So why spend more mana and more casting time using any other advanced roots??? If you need to park a mob, then just mez it.<br>
<br>
Stun I find vital for giving me extra casting time. If a mob is in my face, I can cast stun and then run some amount of feet away in the time that it takes for my spells to refresh (normally about 2-3 seconds). I can then root/mez/gate or whatever, because I now have 8 seconds from the stun plus the new distance that is between the mob and I to decide what to cast next.<br>
<br>
If casters are pulled I love meming our mana-taps. I even tap group members (on a PvP-teams server) Gosh, sometimes I keep a casting mob mezzed at my side just so I can tap him for as long as I can keep mezzing him. Clarity II+Wandering Mind+Theft of Thought yields greater mana return than Koadic's Endless Intellect. Interesting indeed.<br>
<br>
Rune I find vital because it creates a buffer to allow healers and tanks to realize they need to save me before I insta-die from accidental aggro. You will die before a healer can even click his heal button let alone waiting for it to go off. Too many times I have died before a heal was finished casting. Even though I am 55, I still use Rune III because peridots are too expensive.<br>
<br>
------------------<br>
SOLO<br>
-Tash<br>
-Slow/Wake of Tranquility<br>
-Berserker Spirit<br>
-Nuke<br>
-Gate<br>
-Stun<br>
-Mez<br>
-Root<br>
<br>
First of all I create a pet and give it a weapon for dual wield. I then buff it with haste, AC (Shadow), and Berserker Spirit (for the strength and absorbtion shield). If needed I will &quot;harmony&quot; a group of mobs for safe pulling. Tash my target. Stun him once he hits me. Back off and begin to cast slow on it. Then I proceed to chain cast Berserker Spirit (when it fades) on my pet so that he takes the least amount of damage that I can prevent. Then I sit down if I need to med. Finally, if my pet needs help, I will nuke it a few times. Sometimes I do this when I am in a group of 2 players. I have a good Shaman buddy, and we just sit back and watch our pets own =) If I have the time, I'll keep a mezzed casting mob at my side and mana tap it.<br>
<br>
------------------------<br>
QUESTIONS<br>
<br>
1. AGGRO-- A few times I have used Beguiling Visage when in groups. Normally I am needed to Tashania the mob when it's at least 95% hurt or it will aggro me. If I am to slow the mob, then that is when I notice the most aggro ever. Have you guys found Beguiling Visage to help? I haven't tried it enough. I would use this spell more often as a swap in/swap out spell if it were not for it's long recast/mem delay.<br>
-And what about those 5% aggro increase/decrease buffs. Anyone else think that's a waste of a spell for us?<br>
<br>
2. Illusion Scaled Wolf-- Is there one?<br>
<br>
3. Pet HP Regen-- I find that my pet's regen will match my regen. I know this because my pet will heal faster when I sit, and it will heal even faster if I use Illusion Troll and sit. Anyone coroborate?<br>
<br>
4. Intellectual Superiority-- I actually notice that my fizzle rate went up when having this buff. I never touched it since. Don't see any benefit for it as it takes up a buff slot. Anyone coroborate? I haven't tried it lately though. Maybe the lesser chance of interupt is the key part of this. I don't know.<br>
<br>
5. Whirl-- You know, the spin/root/stun spells we have. These seem to not last long enough to be worth casting.<br>
<br>
------------------------------<br>
PEEVES!<br>
<br>
1. CANNOT SEE YOUR TARGET-- nonsense. He's right there! Why can't I cast on a mob that can see? Because of sloppy coding. BAH! Good lord I am not aiming at his FEET! I really hate this on zones that are very hilly.<br>
<br>
2. YOUR TARGET IS TOO FAR AWAY!!-- Whatever! I just casted on a rooted mob and suddenly he's too far for my next cast? I don't think so. This is annoying when standing on the edge of your casting range.<br>
<br>
3. YOUR MAGICAL SKIN ABSORBS THE BLOW!!<br>
YOUR MAGICAL SKIN ABSORBS THE BLOW!-- jesus h., must I be spammed by my own buffs?<br>
<br>
4. A so-and-so's brain begins to melt.... You have slain a so-and-so.... A so-and-so's brain begins to melt. More ungodly spam I could do without. No reason for it to repeat the same line after it dies.<br>
<br>
5. Your target is unmezzable-- Loading please wait... God I hate that. They really have to decrease the aggro on mobs you can't mez. If I can't mez it, then why it got to be so mad at me?<br>
<br>
In conclusion, sorry for the long post, I usually keep the tanks hasted and the casters cracked/runed. I hand out Rune III like it were hershey kisses. Jasper is so cheap. Usually have 4 stacks on me. Oh, ya! Almost forgot charm.<br>
<br>
I love charming pestilence rats and killing lightcrawlers in PoD. Of course you won't ever find me charming unless I'm grouped with someone who can snare my pet. Because even with 250 CHA, I've had trouble. Allot easier recharming a snared pet. Keep the pet hasted and the mob slowed. Heal (ranger/druid/shaman) the pet once in a while, have it sit down, and put on troll illusion. Snare is key on charms. Let the xp flow baby! Oh and do at least 1 pt of damage or your pet takes allot of exp away.<br>
