<br>
Yes, tanks love Boon.  I also hate Boon and Trickster, cause they tie up slots for good - and my slots are at premium.   I so look forward to 63 and NDT (47% through 62 now, NDT scroll banked)<br>
<br>
I never mem Gate in groups.   Quite often, I am the one left standing holding mobs back, while everyone makes their escape.   If I have mana and mobs are mezzable, I can usually load Gate, wait for all to get clear and get out myself.<br>
<br>
Stuns - when you get higher, you'll find those stuns less useful.  Until your lvl 62 stun, mobs above 55 are immune to stuns.   One good place to load stuns is when farmng Xi in ME, or CT casting lizards in yard/maze/TR.<br>
<br>
Lvl 8 root is fast and cheap, but come 58, Fetter is gonna be your new favorite.  Come 61, Greater Fetter.  But, I still use lvl 8 root for farming.   Awesome for those sonics in HM - they tend to run, and they have SoW.<br>
<br>
Do you have LoY?   If you don, what the heck are you still using WM for?  Go and quest your Scryer's Trespass scroll.   It beats WM with an ugly stick.   50mana/tick for a full minute.<br>
<br>
Berserker:  150 mana, 200hp absorb, no component<br>
Rune III: 150 mana, max 230hp absorb, costs a Jasper.   What did you need Rune III for again?  At 55, I carried a stack of dots, and had Rune V handy.  a 700hp absorb is worth it.  And then there's Bedlam at 58.  Of course, Arcane Rune makes it all moot.<br>
<br>
Your lvl 55 pet dual-wields by default, no need to give it a weapon.   Though if you got a 60+ mage nearby, they can summon some VERY nice pet toys.  I love what my pet can do when outfitted with Muzzle and a blade of Walnan or fist of Ixiblat.<br>
<br>
Questions:<br>
1. BV is a good spells for major raids.   The recast is way long for anything else.  But cutting your aggro by 50% is a VERY good thing.  Later on, invest in SCS AA, have your Rune up, and have Boggle ready.   Sometimes HV can help if MT has problems, but at 300 mana it's a terrible mana hog.<br>
The 5% ones never seemed to make difference.  10% ones do seem to have impact.<br>
<br>
2. according to Lucy, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3586&amp;source=Live" target="top">Illusion:Scaled Wolf</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is not there.   Name;y, there is no item called 'Spell: Illusion Scaled Wolf', which can be scribed.<br>
<br>
3. If you mean animation, Zumaik had a fairly bad regen.  Lvl 62 Aieldorb has INSANE regen.   When not fighting, it seems to regen about 10% of its total HP/tick.<br>
<br>
4. Did not seem to have any impact for me - stopped using it.  SCM AA is a far better way to reduce fizzles.<br>
<br>
5. Whirl, Draught, Lamentation - targeted stuns, which can interrupt casting mobs, in situations where AE is a nono - or you don't want to get too close to the mob.  Useless against mob above lvl 55.  You ask me, GoK is an EXCELLENT alternative.  It costs only 125 mana, has instant recast, and works on mobs up to lvl 57.  At 55, it is your ONLY spell that will stop a lvl 56 arachnae terranis in PoD from casting CH.<br>
